    "client_msg_id": "1853454c-3c99-4f94-a8da-422ecd62c7ff",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Cool stuff! :+1:\n\nI am a big fan of reactivity in JavaScript. A long time ago I played with MobX (I see it is one of your's inspirations) and really enjoyed it. Now I am on the Vue side, and one of the reason I use Vue is its really nice reactive system (which similar to MobX) and especially the new Composition API (inspired by React hooks).\n\nSo something that is not clear for me: what differences between your library and MobX? And with Vue?",
    "user": "UJ6LDMMN0",
    "ts": "1621059006.138300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
