        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "7X44b",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Cool stuff! "
              },
              {
                "type": "emoji",
                "name": "+1"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nI am a big fan of reactivity in JavaScript. A long time ago I played with MobX (I see it is one of your's inspirations) and really enjoyed it. Now I am on the Vue side, and one of the reason I use Vue is its really nice reactive system (which similar to MobX) and especially the new Composition API (inspired by React hooks).\n\nSo something that is not clear for me: what differences between your library and MobX? And with Vue?"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
